{"type": "article", "id": 33229, "title": "把你的小朋友放到这个茶几里吧｜这个设计了不起", "description": "我们每天都为你推荐几个最近发现的好设计。", "date": "2016-10-12T23:19:24Z", "super_tag": "", "tags": [{"id": 271, "name": "工业设计"}, {"id": 1526, "name": "Duffy London"}, {"id": 18678, "name": "Fuseproject"}, {"id": 28427, "name": "TILE"}, {"id": 33878, "name": "iJet"}, {"id": 33856, "name": "Yves-Béhar"}, {"id": 33857, "name": "Kunsik Choi"}], "category": 17, "column": 38, "author": 400262, "comment_count": 4, "praise_count": 178, "image": "img/article/article_show/20161012191853BLuXtQ3gsFRfvID7.jpg", "contents": "<p class=\"\">          </p><p>「这个设计了不起」的微信公众号上线啦，直接搜索「BestDesign」或是「Qthings」就可以订阅，关注我们每日发现的新鲜好设计。</p><h3>BLINCAM by BLINCAM</h3><p>          </p><p>还记得特工电影中眨眼就能拍照的虹膜吗？由<a href=\"http://www.blincam.co/\" style=\"background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\" rel=\"nofollow\">日本团队</a>研发的 BLINCAM 眼镜配件把这种黑科技变成了现实，你只要把这个内置摄像头和动作捕捉装置的长方体架在镜框上，它就会在你眨眼后自动拍摄照片。考虑到有些人不擅长眨一边的眼睛，BLINCAM 还能将感应设置成完全紧闭双眼的动作。拍下的照片可以通过配件自带的蓝牙功能发送到配套的应用中，就像是一个可穿戴相机。你可以通过<a href=\"https://www.indiegogo.com/projects/blincam-taking-a-picture-with-a-wink-camera-photo#/\" style=\"background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\" rel=\"nofollow\">链接</a>参与众筹，早鸟价为 159 美元。</p><p>          </p><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin: 0px;\" class=\"\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20161012150837YOoixayLMkcrQq9U.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.590323\" data-format=\"jpeg\" class=\"\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin: 0px;\" class=\"\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20161012150837758yaATdJlvqRVhr.png\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.533871\" data-format=\"png\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20161012150837ONHg8tzGcPbx1Zo2.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.666129\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/201610121508370IoGc3AjRvyZXFzE.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.562903\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20161012150837v2Qj9n4m6gZwRNuL.png\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.664516\" data-format=\"png\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin: 0px;\" class=\"\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/201610121508376yZIfaV83L4k5lmn.png\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.591935\" data-format=\"png\">\r\n</figure></div><h3>Tile Mate by Yves-Béhar</h3><p>          </p><p>如果你总是掉东西又觉得市面上的追踪器不够美观小巧，不妨来看看设计公司 <a href=\"https://fuseproject.com/\" rel=\"nofollow\">fuseproject</a> 为蓝牙追踪器品牌 <a href=\"https://www.thetileapp.com/\" rel=\"nofollow\">Tile</a> 设计的新一代产品 Tile Mate。它由两块通过磁性吸附在一起的防水瓷片组成，组合后的厚度仅为两毫米，可以像卡片一样随身携带。瓷片中央是一个提供按压反馈的触控按钮，按下后就会发出提示音便于用户寻找物品。手机可以通过蓝牙同时连接四个追踪器，就算遗失了手机也能通过它进行反向追踪。这是它的<a href=\"https://www.thetileapp.com/store/tiles/mate\" rel=\"nofollow\">购买链接</a>，售价为 25 美元。</p><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin: 0px;\" class=\"\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20161013101859KrAd6GNbpqVx2wEm.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.666259\" data-format=\"jpeg\" class=\"\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin: 0px;\" class=\"\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20161013101858oOliK5hkGt8MBI9v.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.733496\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20161013101857NLcZs2XH0UrxGdvJ.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"1.000000\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin: 0px;\" class=\"\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20161013101858dwL8JtZiDjIeAbxy.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.733496\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20161013101858pUyhIKgqZEuaLs9S.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.870416\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure></div><h3>OWL paperlamps by Hugo Formica &amp; Teresa Almeida</h3><p>          </p><p>由葡萄牙建筑师 Hugo Formica 和 Teresa Almeida 创立的 OWL paperlamps 是一个专营 DIY 折纸灯具品牌，Almeida 负责设计部分，Formica 则通过 3D 建模将创意转变成产品。目前有企鹅、乌龟、鹦鹉和猫头鹰四种款式可选，虽然它们看起来并不复杂，但组装可能会花上几个小时，让人回想起了学校里的手工课程。你可以通过它的<a href=\"https://www.etsy.com/jp/shop/OWLpaperlamps\" rel=\"nofollow\">店铺链接</a>购买到这些折纸灯，售价从 40.77 美元起。</p><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/201610121803148fhV7AMT34EQ6SHJ.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"1.000000\" data-format=\"jpeg\" class=\"\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin: 0px;\" class=\"\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20161012180315r6bXy3a8dGeotghz.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"1.000000\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20161012180314osKwlfn36cHtUJhq.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"1.000000\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20161012180314VWmgRktxKnZQOX5M.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"1.000000\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20161012180315eI5A2PsB9Voz6wbS.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"1.000000\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20161012180314DXKuZAvcfGqtCY6H.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.615789\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure></div><h3>Shelter by Duffy London</h3><p>          </p><p>在灾难发生时，如何更有效率地为受灾民众提供安全的收容所是一个亟待解决的问题。此前曾设计过深海桌等家具的英国设计工作室 <a href=\"https://duffylondon.com/\" rel=\"nofollow\">Duffy London</a> 带来了这款名为 Shleter 的帐篷，内部的空间足以容纳两个成年人。考虑到模块化设计在运输和搭建上的优势，Shelter 包含了一套木制配件，只需要一把螺丝刀就能在一个小时内迅速组装起来。一辆标准单位的卡车可以容纳 35 个帐篷套装，可以更快地运输到需要的地方。</p><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20161012145101gnCseYGoqBl7mPf5.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.533007\" data-format=\"jpeg\" class=\"\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20161012145102kNbtoMx5aVPvZ8c6.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.666259\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin: 0px;\" class=\"\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/201610121451015n06DQTdW4SYcIhL.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.388889\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin: 0px;\" class=\"\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/201610121451024SHcs9tKDfl0qriX.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.668704\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin: 0px;\" class=\"\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20161012145100IQauet7GTB5zRnr9.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.613692\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure></div><h3>Boida by Kunsik Choi</h3><p>          </p><p>既然孩子们总是在好奇大人在干什么，为什么不让他们离大人们更近一点呢？韩裔瑞典设计师 <a href=\"http://kunsik.com/\" rel=\"nofollow\">Kunsik Choi</a> 最近带来的这款 <a href=\"http://kunsik.com/?portfolio=boida\" rel=\"nofollow\">Boida</a> 茶几起到的就是这么一个贴心的功能，当大人们在一旁工作时，孩子可以坐在旁边特别设计过的椅子里。</p><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin: 0px;\" class=\"\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20161012145241OFS6q980kglKIYPc.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.666667\" data-format=\"jpeg\" class=\"\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin: 0px;\" class=\"\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20161012145240A0kdpVJzLbyQh2ua.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.666667\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20161012145240rqeHbjS49pKc0WUI.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.666667\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20161012145240tBdrn6WkZMLSN5hR.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.667188\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20161012145241hBQtmMik7Z8br2FI.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.666667\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20161012145241WDA8KlxLIo95bQGg.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.666667\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure></div><p>          </p><h3>ONE HUNDRED TOKYO by iJet</h3><p>如果你刚好喜欢拼图和地图，日本 3D 打印公司 <a href=\"http://www.ijet.co.jp/\" rel=\"nofollow\">iJet</a> 最近推出的 ONE HUNDRED TOKYO 企划会给你添一份不太一样的收藏。公司以 1:12500 的比例用 100 块 1*1 厘米的拼图组成了立体版的东京地图，忠实还原了地标建筑和绿植。每块拼图后面还附有磁铁，可以当作冰箱贴使用。你可以通过<a href=\"https://www.kickstarter.com/projects/1875462194/one-hundred-tokyo-full-color-3d-printed-maps\" rel=\"nofollow\">链接</a>参与众筹，单块的早鸟价为 85 美元，整套价格则高达 1 万美元。</p><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin: 0px;\" class=\"\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/201610122201544gbFopXlYfMIwJST.jpeg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.652941\" data-format=\"jpeg\" class=\"\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin: 0px;\" class=\"\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20161012220154KdBponkeSlx1t5C3.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.683824\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin: 0px;\" class=\"\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20161012220157xYubyGTNpkW4ZCSJ.gif\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.707353\" data-format=\"gif\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20161012220154rO4cIYDSJCHpNgdK.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.714706\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20161012220154vFB47lYHjt6NMkSL.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.994118\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin: 0px;\" class=\"\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20161012220154C0VnYyvBUMTpj9A6.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.569118\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure></div>"}